<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-544-107  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 544 107.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Feb 20 1990 v4 n7 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Monotype adds Classic Fonts. (Monotype Typography Inc.) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pfiffner, Pamela.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Monotype Typography Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Classic Fonts (Computer font) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionDesktop publishingFonts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Pamela PfiffnerandM;Chicago -- Monotype Typography Inc. is releasing its Type 3 font library in anew format called Classic Fonts that is based on technology licensed fromAdobe Systems Inc.andM;Classic Fonts is similar to Adobe's Type 1 hinted fonts, but the formatretains Monotype's outline.andM;Classic Fonts was developed so the company could take advantage of the AdobeType Manager utility and offer better screen display, according to JeffLevel, type director at Monotype.andP;  The new format also produces better outputon low-resolution printers and better type resolution at smaller point sizes.andM;Classic Fonts also give users immediate access to Type 1 attributes ratherthan making them wait for Monotype's fully hinted typefaces to becomeavailable.andP;  That should happen over the next year, Level said.andM;With the introduction of its Classic Fonts format earlier this month,Monotype began phasing out its Type 3 fonts.andP;  The format will still beavailable to OEMs and as a special order for those who use software thatdoesn't yet accept the Type 1 format.andM;Registered owners of Monotype's Type 3 fonts will be able to upgrade to theClassic Fonts format at a cost equal to the difference between the price ofthe original package and the new Classic Fonts package.andM;Monotype Typography Inc. is located at 53 W. Jackson Blvd., Suite 504,Chicago, Ill.andP;  60604; (312) 855-1440.andO;</TEXT></DOC>